passwd -S
• Displays the password status of the currently logged-in user
(locked, set, or expired).

passwd -S user1
• Displays the password status of the user user1.

passwd --status
• Another way to show the password status of the current user
(same as passwd -S).

passwd --status user1
• Shows the password status of the user user1.

chage -l user1
• Displays password aging information for user1,

such as: Last password change
         Password expiry date
         Account expiration date
